<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-14744] camel-salesforce : lazy-login</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-14744</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m using&#160;org.apache.camel.springboot:camel-salesforce-starter:3.1.0&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Configuration&#160;&lt;b&gt;camel.component.salesforce.lazy-login&lt;/b&gt; only&#160;seems to work when it&apos;s used in combination with &lt;b&gt;camel.component.salesforce.lazy-start-producer&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When used on it&apos;s own, method&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;b&gt;&lt;em&gt;org.apache.camel.component.salesforce.internal.client.AbstractClientBase#start()&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 will call method&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;em&gt;&lt;b&gt;org.apache.camel.component.salesforce.internal.SalesforceSession#login()&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 without an appropriate guard statement.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is this intended behaviour?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
